value.name: DC Under Voltage
value.description:
Cause: DC under-voltage shutdown occurs if DC voltage is below
LBCO voltage level.
Solution: Check for the correct battery voltage at the
inverter's DC input terminals. Check for an external
DC load on the batteries. Check condition of batteries
and recharge if possible.

value.name: AI Over Voltage
value.description:
Cause: Over-voltage anti-islanding, fast disconnect, 270 Vac.
Solution: No action required. The inverter stops selling and
disconnects from the grid. When the fault clears, a five-minute
timer begins counting down. The inverter does not sell again until
grid voltage and frequency are within range for five minutes.

value.name: AC Output Voltage Shutdown
value.description:
Grid Voltage Line to Line is beyond limits. This is a utility fault; it will 
clear itself when the AC voltage comes within the specified range. (see the 
electrical specifications section in your user manual). The message clears 
after 15 seconds if the (> 264 V or < 211 V).
